# Terraform AWS Assignment

Created by Tanmay Soni

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates Infrastructure as Code (IaC) using Terraform on AWS Cloud.

The infrastructure includes:

- AWS VPC
- Public Subnet
- Internet Gateway
- Route Table
- Security Group
- EC2 Instance (t2.micro)

The goal of this project is to automate cloud infrastructure provisioning using Terraform.

---

# Technologies Used

- Terraform
- AWS Cloud
- EC2
- VPC Networking

---

# AWS Resources Created

## 1. VPC
A custom Virtual Private Cloud was created for network isolation.

## 2. Public Subnet
A public subnet was configured inside the VPC.

## 3. Internet Gateway
Internet access was enabled using an Internet Gateway.

## 4. Route Table
A route table was associated with the public subnet.

## 5. Security Group
Security group rules allow:
- SSH (Port 22)
- HTTP (Port 80)

## 6. EC2 Instance
An Ubuntu/Linux EC2 t2.micro instance was launched.

---

# Terraform Commands Used

## Initialize Terraform

```bash
terraform init
